The Python test suite uses pytest with coverage reporting.

## Test Files

```
tests/
├── conftest.py              # Shared fixtures
├── sample_addresses.csv     # Test data
├── test_parser.py           # Parser unit tests
├── test_geocoder.py         # Geocoder tests (mocked HTTP)
├── test_matrix.py           # Distance matrix tests
├── test_solver.py           # TSP solver tests
├── test_exporter.py         # Export format tests
└── test_platform_compat.py  # Cross-platform compatibility
```

## Running Tests

```bash
cd ontrack

# Run all tests
pytest

# Run with coverage
pytest --cov=core --cov-report=term-missing

# Run specific test file
pytest tests/test_solver.py -v

# Run platform-specific markers
pytest -m linux
pytest -m android
```

## Test Markers

Tests are tagged with platform markers:

```python
@pytest.mark.linux    # Linux-specific tests
@pytest.mark.windows  # Windows-specific tests
@pytest.mark.android  # Android/buildozer tests
```

## Coverage

Coverage is configured in `pyproject.toml`:

```toml
[tool.coverage.run]
source = ["core", "config"]
omit = ["tests/*", "gui/*", "assets/*"]

[tool.coverage.report]
fail_under = 70
```

The minimum threshold is **70%** coverage on the `core/` and `config/` modules. GUI and asset code is excluded from coverage reporting.

## What the Tests Cover

### test_solver.py
- Solver with a small set of known addresses and a pre-computed matrix
- OR-Tools and nearest-neighbor backends produce valid routes
- Edge cases: single address, two addresses, depot index validation
- Open TSP (no return to origin)

### test_geocoder.py
- Nominatim response parsing
- Google geocoding response parsing
- Failed geocode handling (graceful skip)
- IP geolocation

### test_matrix.py
- OSRM matrix response parsing
- Haversine distance calculation
- Matrix shape validation (N×N)

### test_parser.py
- CSV with header row
- Excel file parsing
- Plain text (one address per line)
- Empty input handling

### test_exporter.py
- CSV export format
- Google Maps URL construction
- URL chunking for >10 stops
- FieldMaps and Waze URL formats

### test_platform_compat.py
- Platform detection logic
- Import availability checks
- Feature flag behavior per platform

## Security Scanning

[Bandit](https://bandit.readthedocs.io/) scans the Python code for common security issues:

```bash
bandit -r core/ -f txt
```

This is also run as a Nix flake check via `nix flake check`.
